The motto of the Orion team back in the late 50's and early 60's was &quot;Mars by 65 and Saturn by 70&quot;. They knew how to get it done and were kneecapped in favour of Apollo. Effectively killing the space age off, perhaps forever.<br>
Let's try and be patient and friendly to newcomers. It's easy to assume that no other programs have ever rivalled those big chemical boosters so adored by Nasa. The media rarely mentions there was ever an alternative to such monstrous fireworks so mistakes must be expected occasionally/frequently from visitors here. It's probably better to make friends than offend them and make a lifelong opponent. We don't need any more Cygonauts (my fault on that one, sorry guys). Let's work on our PR as you suggested the other day Bestonnet. I've been in some flamewars and they aren't worth the aggravation.<br>
<br>
